  "stem": "<p>The force <em>F</em>, in newtons, exerted on an object of mass <em>m</em>, in kilograms, with acceleration <em>a</em>, in meters per second squared, is given by <math><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>a</mi></math>. Which of the following correctly expresses <em>a</em> in terms of <em>F</em> and <em>m</em>?</p>",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p><math><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>F</mi><mi>m</mi></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b",
      "content": "<p><math><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "c",
      "content": "<p><math><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "d",
      "content": "<p><math><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mi>F</mi></mfrac></math></p>"
    }
  ],
